= Jefferson Davis Treason Case

Jefferson Davis remains under arrest for his leadership of the rebellious Confederate states. Radical Republicans push for a high-profile treason trial, seeing it as essential to uphold federal authority. Moderates and Conservatives warn that such a trial could spark Southern vengeance or risk a Supreme Court ruling that legitimizes secession.

